The paper deals with scheduling computation tasks in a distributed learning problem, which is a common topic in distributed computing (cs.DC) and machine learning (cs.LG). The problem involves dealing with delays and stragglers, which are also relevant to control systems (cs.SY) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the use of a master node to coordinate the computation suggests a networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) perspective.
